Three fixes to eliminate thin/mock data:

1. storageFetchJson: Dynamic env var reads (no stale module-level capture) +
   auto-create Supabase bucket on first write if missing

2. flow/state: When no tonight pack in Supabase, compile signals live
   (OpenAgenda + OpenWeather + PRIM + skeleton → ramifications) instead
   of returning empty brief. Also writes result to Supabase in background
   so next request is fast.

3. health endpoint: Full pipeline diagnostics — shows whether pack exists,
   signal/ramification counts, all env var presence checks.

New: src/lib/city-signals/compileLive.ts — standalone live compiler
Header: X-Flow-Source on /api/flow/state (storage-pack | live-compiled | empty-brief)
